# Prospec

This `{{base_dir}}/` directory holds the **Prospec** working files for this project — the project Constitution, the AI Knowledge base, and change specifications that drive a Spec-Driven Development (SDD) workflow. If you are new to this project, this file explains what Prospec is and where to read more.

## What is Prospec?

Prospec is a Skills-driven Spec-Driven Development (SDD) toolkit for AI coding agents. Day-to-day work runs through slash-command **Skills inside your AI agent** (Claude Code, Antigravity, Copilot, Codex); a thin **CLI** only bootstraps the project and regenerates Skills and Knowledge. The payoff: the agent follows a consistent `story → plan → tasks → implement → review → verify → archive` workflow, grounded in structured, version-controlled project knowledge.

Three pieces work together:

- **Skills** run the workflow inside your agent — the day-to-day surface.
- **AI Knowledge** is progressive, version-controlled project memory (modules, specs, lessons) the Skills read and grow with each change.
- **CLI (`prospec`)** is a one-time/occasional bootstrap tool that scaffolds the project and regenerates Skills + Knowledge — it is *not* in the runtime loop.

